The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Cristianos double

London: Manchester Uniteds Cristiano Ronaldo pulled off a rare double on Sunday when he was named both PFA Player of the Year and Young Player of the Year. Ronaldo is only the second man in the history of the players awards to take both titles after Aston Villas Andy Gray in 1977. 

Didier Drogba was second ahead of Paul Scholes. 

In the Young Player award, Ronaldo, 22, held off Arsenal midfielder Cesc Fabregas. 

The Premier League team of the year was: United keeper Edwin van der Sar; defenders Gary Neville, Nemanja Vidic, Rio Ferdinand and Patrice Evra; midfielders Giggs, Scholes, Cristiano and Gerrard; and Chelseas Drogba and Tottenhams Dimitar Berbatov as the two strikers. (AGENCIES) 




